WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
Decision audit: how sales enablement teams can improve manager coaching follow-through through sounds strategic, but the real constraint is operating behavior in the workflow.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
As output scales, decision clarity becomes the real bottleneck. If outcomes are flat, run a decision audit before launching another learning initiative.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: volume around audit grows faster than attention and adoption.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So start with one owner, one metric, and one weekly review loop before scaling.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then scale only after one-week evidence shows real movement.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: performance support breaks when roles and expectations keep mutating.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So the strategic question is whether the system improves decisions or only produces artifacts.

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
